izontal scalability and creates noisy neighbor I/O issues during retention. Decoupling compute from storage eliminates this constraint, allowing seamless scaling.\",\n        effort: 9,\n        impact: 10,\n        risk: 8\n      },\n      {\n        category: \"performance\",\n        title: \"Shift from Batch Purge to Ephemeral Partitioning\",\n        description: \"Stop deleting rows entirely. Implement time-based table partitioning (e.g., persona_events_YYYY_MM_DD) so retention becomes an instant DROP TABLE command instead of millions of chunked DELETE operations.\",\n        reasoning: \"SQLite DELETE is inherently I/O heavy, creates fragmentation, and forces complex event-loop yielding. DROP TABLE reclaims space instantly, eliminating the need for the batching workaround entirely.\",\n        effort: 7,\n        impact: 9,\n        risk: 6\n      },\n      {\n        category: \"functionality\",\n        title: \"Centralized Data Warehouse Sync for Analytics\",\n        description: \"Instead of aggregating metrics using SQLite watermarks inside the orchestrator, replicate the SQLite WAL of all tenant DBs directly to a column-store like ClickHouse. Remove local metric aggregation completely.\",\n        reasoning: \"Using an OLTP database for cross-tenant time-series aggregation creates severe contention. WAL replication moves analytics load off the operational database, enabling cross-tenant queries without orchestrator impact.\",\n        effort: 8,\n        impact: 9,\n        risk: 7\n      }\n    ];\n\n    for (const idea of ideas) {\n      const ideaPayload = {\n        scan_id: scanId,\n        project_id: \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n        context_id: \"ctx_1773782663367_bj2fyhb\",\n        scan_type: \"tech_innovator\",\n        category: idea.category,\n        title: idea.title,\n        description: idea.description,\n        reasoning: idea.reasoning,\n        effort: idea.effort,\n        impact: idea.impact,\n        risk: idea.risk\n      };\n\n      console.log(`Creating idea: ${idea.title}`);\n      await makeRequest({\n        hostname: 'localhost',\n        port: 3000,\n        path: '/api/ideas',\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: {\n          'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n        }\n      }, ideaPayload);\n    }\n\n    console.log(\"All ideas created successfully.\");\n  } catch (err) {\n    console.error(\"Error:\", err.message);\n  }\n}\n\nrun();\n","file_path":"run-ideas.js"}}
